Hurricane Milton Carves Destructive Path Across Florida

LIVE

Oct. 10, 2024, 9:41 a.m. ET

Storm Spawns Tornadoes and Leaves More Than 3 Million Without Power

  • Milton maintained dangerous hurricane strength early today as it roared through Florida’s Atlantic Coast, where the storm had already caused deaths and damage.
  • On the Gulf Coast, where Milton made landfall, communities were beginning to assess the damage from winds, heavy rain and storm surges.

The storm destroyed the roof of the Tampa Bay Rays’ stadium, which was being used to house emergency workers.
